tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  38,62,"And the arrogant transgressors will say: “Why do we not see with us in the fire men we used to consider in the world amongst the wretched who deserved punishment?"
  38,68,"You are turning away from this news of great status; you do not turn towards it."
  38,76,"Iblis said: “I am better than Adam. You created me from fire and you created him from clay. And fire is a more noble substance than clay”."
  38,79,"Iblis said: “Give me respite and do not make me die until the day You raise Your servants”."
  38,80,"Allah said: “You are amongst those given respite."
  38,81,"Until the day of the known time which is fixed for your destruction”."
  38,82,"Iblis said: “I swear by Your power and domination that I shall misguide all of the children of Adam."
  38,83,"Except whom You protect from my misguiding and You have chosen to worship You alone”."